**Module 4: OWASP Bingo**

Companion Instructions & Learning Notes

*Secure Web Application Development --- BBC Academy / JBI Training*

vulnerable_shop.py \| vulnerable_shop_fixed.py

**Overview**

This exercise uses a deliberately vulnerable Flask web application ---
ShopCo --- to give delegates hands-on experience identifying and
categorising real security flaws in source code. Unlike black-box tools
such as OWASP Juice Shop, this exercise puts you in the developer\'s
seat: you can see exactly why each vulnerability exists and what a
minimal fix looks like.

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **📋 Three files, three stages**                                      |
|                                                                       |
| Stage 1 --- Identify: Read vulnerable_shop_CLEAN.py (no hints). Find  |
| and annotate the 8 flaws.                                             |
|                                                                       |
| Stage 2 --- Exploit: Run vulnerable_shop.py in your VM and use a      |
| browser to trigger each flaw.                                         |
|                                                                       |
| Stage 3 --- Fix: Compare vulnerable_shop_fixed.py line-by-line and    |
| understand each correction.                                           |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

**Stage 1 --- Identify the Flaws (15 minutes)**

Work individually or in pairs. Read through the clean source code
printout (or open vulnerable_shop_CLEAN.py in a text editor). For each
flaw you find, write:

-   The line number or function name where the flaw occurs

-   The OWASP Top 10:2025 category you believe it belongs to

-   A one-sentence description of what an attacker could do with it

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **💡 Hints --- where to look**                                        |
|                                                                       |
| There are TWO flaws in the first 6 lines of the file.                 |
|                                                                       |
| The login() function contains THREE separate flaws.                   |
|                                                                       |
| The profile() function contains TWO separate flaws.                   |
|                                                                       |
| The ping() function contains ONE flaw --- but it\'s the most severe.  |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

