**Instructor Setup Notes**

**VM Preparation**

One-time setup per delegate VM (can be scripted via Appendix A of the
Flask Supplement):

> pip3 install flask bcrypt flask-unsign \--break-system-packages
>
> mkdir -p \~/vuln_flask_app/module4_owasp_bingo
>
> \# Copy the three Python files to the above directory
>
> cd \~/vuln_flask_app/module4_owasp_bingo
>
> python3 vulnerable_shop.py \# Port 5000 --- initialises shop.db on
> first run
>
> \# In a second terminal:
>
> python3 vulnerable_shop_fixed.py \# Port 5001 --- initialises
> shop_fixed.db

**Running Both Apps Side-by-Side**

Having both apps running simultaneously on ports 5000 and 5001 is very
effective for the Stage 3 comparison. Delegates can switch between tabs
to see the same operation behave differently.

**Timing Guide**

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Stage**       **Time**    **Activity**
  --------------- ----------- -------------------------------------------
  **Stage 1 ---   15 mins     Delegates annotate the clean source code
  Identify**                  individually or in pairs

  **Reveal answer 5 mins      Instructor walks through each flaw --- ask
  key**                       delegates who found it first

  **Stage 2 ---   25 mins     Step through exploits A--H; instructor
  Exploit**                   demos B (cookie forge) & H (command
                              injection)

  **Stage 3 ---   10 mins     Delegates open fixed file; instructor
  Compare**                   highlights key changes for each flaw

  **Debrief       5 mins      Select 2--3 discussion questions based on
  discussion**                group composition
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **📌 Mixed-ability note**                                             |
|                                                                       |
| Developer delegates typically find Flaws 3, 4, and 8 first            |
| (code-level issues).                                                  |
|                                                                       |
| Tester and sysadmin delegates often spot Flaws 1 and 2 first          |
| (configuration issues).                                               |
|                                                                       |
| This natural split is a feature, not a problem --- use it to prompt   |
| cross-role discussion.                                                |
|                                                                       |
| If the group finishes Stage 1 early, skip straight to the most        |
| impactful exploit (Flaw 8).                                           |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
